{
  "stem": "10272.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "That he was, like, our spiritual leader, the closest to God.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was-- when something had a problem, we turned always to our rabbi.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Not only-- in anything, which want to get some help.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Even to a person who was sick-- you didn't go first to a doctor in our town, you went to a rabbi.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So of course we believed him.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "He said something, we believed in it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that was the problem that Jews were not enough alert when it was still time to do something.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "They underestimated this danger of Hitler, which was around the corner.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And he overestimated the danger of assimilation.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[INAUDIBLE] if a Jew will  marry a non-Jewish girl or he will become a secular Jew and then go to Palestine-- at that time, Palestine was a no-no because no Jew was allowed to go to Palestine.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That is only a messiah will come-- something like that.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this thing confused-- or they kept the Jews under such a-- it was a climate.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They created a climate.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In this climate, these words which these rabbis were, at that time, uttering created a climate that the Jews were so disarmed, so blind, so believing in these words, when it came already to a situation that they wanted to do something, it was already too late.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I want to take you back a little bit to your childhood.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Tell me where you lived at the time, the address.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, I was living-- we were living on the street close to the train station.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They call it already in Czech.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The train station is [? nadrazi ?] and the street is [?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Ulice. ?] 158 [? nadrazi ?] [?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Ulice. ?] that was our address.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Bushtina.",
      "word_count": 1
    }
  ],
